    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151388>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. (a –a) Polygonum terzioglui (Makbul & S. Kundakçı 514), (b –b) P. samsunicum (Makbul & S. Kundakçı 316). 1. Leaves 1 3 1 3 (stero microscope), 2. Leaves (SEM), 3. epidermal ornamentation (SEM)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151388/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151384>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Polygonum terzioglui (a) photograph from the type locality (Photographed by S. Makbul), (b) holotype (Makbul & S. Kundakçı 514)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151384/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151390>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. (a –a) Polygonum terzioglui (Makbul & S. Kundakçı 514), (b –b) P. samsunicum (Makbul & S. Kundakçı 316). 1. Ochrea 1 3 1 3 (stero microscope), 2. Epidermal cell shape (SEM), 3. Ochrea ornamentation (SEM)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151390/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151392>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. (a –a) Polygonum terzioglui (Makbul & S. Kundakçı 514), (b –b) P. samsunicum (Makbul & S. Kundakçı 316). 1. Fruit 1 3 1 3 (stero microscope), 2–3. Fruit surface ornamentation (SEM)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151392/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151394>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Majority-rule consensus cladogram of the Polygonum from the ML analysis based on the nrDNA ITS dataset (support values: first-line ML bootstrap and JK jackknife, second-line pp posterior probability). Clade names are in accordance with those taken from Yurtseva et al. (2019), and Atraphaxis, Bactria, Duma, Duravia, Fallopia, Muehlenbeckia, Persepolium, and Polygonella were indicated by a thick black bar." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151394/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

